3wn.title: Decit
3wn.text: A decit, or "decimal digit" (also known as a "dit", "ban", or "hartley") is the amount of [3xd information] required to single out one thing from a set of ten. That is, a decit is a measure of information equal to $\log_2(10)\approx 3.32$ [shannon shannons].
